[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Now, using the second equation:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m \[
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m \log_{10} y + 2 \log_{10} (\text{lcm}(x,y)) = 570
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m \]
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Since \(\text{lcm}(x,y) = \frac{xy}{\text{gcd}(x,y)}\), we get:
