[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m The question is about calculating the total amount of money that Wang Hong's father can withdraw after three years from a fixed-term bank deposit.
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m First, I need to identify what type of interest this is. Since it's specified as an "annual interest rate," I assume this is simple interest rather than compound interest, as the question doesn't mention compounding.
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m The formula for simple interest is:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = P(1 + rt)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Where:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = the total amount of money accumulated after n years, including interest
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m P = the principal amount (the initial amount of money)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m r = the annual interest rate (decimal)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m t = the time the money is invested for (in years)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m From the question, I have:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m P = 20,000 yuan
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m r = 3.33% = 0.0333 (converted to decimal)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m t = 3 years
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Now let me plug these values into the formula:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = 20000(1 + 0.0333 Г— 3)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = 20000(1 + 0.0999)
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = 20000 Г— 1.0999
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m A = 21998
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Wait, let's double-check this calculation. If the annual interest rate is 3.33%, over three years it would be:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Interest = 20000 Г— 0.0333 Г— 3 = 2000 Г— 0.0999 = 1998
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m So the total amount to withdraw would be:
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m Principal + Interest = 20000 + 1998 = 21998
