[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m So, if we have \(1 + 3 + 5 + \ldots + n = 20^2\), it means we're summing the first \(m\) odd numbers (where \(m\) is the count of terms) to get \(20^2\).
[36m(main_task pid=19626)[0m 
